{"name": "gradescope-utils", "metadata": {"name": "gradescope-utils", "version": "0.5.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Topic :: Software Development :: Build Tools"], "home_page": "https://github.com/gradescope/gradescope-utils", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Utilities for building Gradescope autograders", "upload_time": 1666044055}, "documentation": ["# Gradescope Python Utilities\n\n[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/gradescope-utils.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/gradescope-utils)\n[![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/gradescope-utils/badge/?version=latest)](https://gradescope-utils.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest)\n\n## Installing\n\nMake sure you have pip installed (eg. on Debian/Ubuntu, `apt-get install python-pip`).\n\nThen, run `pip install gradescope-utils`\n\n## Packages\n\n- [Autograder Utilities](/gradescope_utils/autograder_utils)\n\n## Changelog\n\nSee the [Releases](https://github.com/gradescope/gradescope-utils/releases) page.\n\n## Releasing new versions\n\nFollow https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/packaging-projects/, but in brief:\n\n1. Bump the version in setup.py\n2. Draft a release on https://github.com/gradescope/gradescope-utils/releases\n  - This can take care of tagging for you. Otherwise, tag the commit: `git tag vX.Y.Z COMMIT_SHA`\n  - Make sure that the setup.py version matches the release/tag version\n  - GitHub releases can help auto-generate release notes from merged PRs. Edit these as necessary.\n3. Publish the release on GitHub. GitHub Actions will build and publish a new release when a version is tagged (e.g. when a GitHub release is published).\n\n## Support\n\nContact us at [help@gradescope.com](mailto:help@gradescope.com) if you need help with these packages.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "gradescope_utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.weight", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.weight.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.weight.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __weight__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @weight(3.0)"]}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.number", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.number.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.number.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __number__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @number(\"1.1\")\n\nThis field will then be used to sort the test results on Gradescope."]}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.visibility", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.visibility.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.visibility.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __visibility__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @visibility(\"hidden\")\n\nOptions for the visibility field are as follows:\n\n- `hidden`: test case will never be shown to students\n- `after_due_date`: test case will be shown after the assignment's due date has passed.\n  If late submission is allowed, then test will be shown only after the late due date.\n- `after_published`: test case will be shown only when the assignment is explicitly published from the \"Review Grades\" page\n- `visible` (default): test case will always be shown"]}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.hide_errors", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.hide_errors.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.hide_errors.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __hide_errors__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @hide_errors(\"Error message to be shown upon test failure\")\n\nUsed to hide the particular source of an error which caused a test to fail.\nOtherwise, a test's particular assertions can be seen by students."]}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.tags", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.tags.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.tags.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Simple decorator to add a __tags__ property to a function\n\nUsage: @tags(\"concept1\", \"concept2\")"]}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.leaderboard", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.leaderboard.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "column_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sort_order", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.leaderboard.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator that indicates that a test corresponds to a leaderboard column\n\nUsage: @leaderboard(\"high_score\"). The string parameter indicates\nthe name of the column on the leaderboard\n\nThen, within the test, set the value by calling\nkwargs['set_leaderboard_value'] with a value. You can make this convenient by\nexplicitly declaring a set_leaderboard_value keyword argument, eg.\n\n```\ndef test_highscore(set_leaderboard_value=None):\n    set_leaderboard_value(42)\n```"]}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.partial_credit", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.partial_credit.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "weight", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.decorators.partial_credit.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator that indicates that a test allows partial credit\n\nUsage: @partial_credit(test_weight)\n\nThen, within the test, set the value by calling\nkwargs['set_score'] with a value. You can make this convenient by\nexplicitly declaring a set_score keyword argument, eg.\n\n```\n@partial_credit(10)\ndef test_partial(set_score=None):\n    set_score(4.2)\n```"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.files", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "gradescope_utils.autograder_utils.files.check_submitted_files", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "paths", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "base", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Checks that the files in the given list exist in the student's submission.\n\nReturns a list of missing files.\n\neg. check_submitted_files(['src/c